  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version`\r\nCL client & version: e.g. lighthouse/nimbus/prysm@v1.0.0\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI'm running go-ethereum v1.11.0 in docker with snap-syncing(resync from genesis). \r\n\r\n<details><summary>docker-compose as below ðŸ‘‡</summary>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\nversion: '3'\r\n\r\nservices:\r\n  geth-full:\r\n    image: ethereum/client-go:v1.11.0\r\n    container_name: geth-full\r\n    command:\r\n      - '--db.engine=pebble'\r\n      - '--syncmode=snap'\r\n      - '--datadir=/data'\r\n      - '--cache.preimages'\r\n      - '--cache=4120'\r\n      - '--cache.database=60'\r\n      - '--cache.trie=30'\r\n      - '--cache.gc=5'\r\n      - '--cache.snapshot=5'\r\n      - '--cache.trie.rejournal=48h'\r\n      - '--maxpeers=200'\r\n      - '--port=40303'\r\n      - '--http'\r\n      - '--http.addr=0.0.0.0'\r\n      - '--http.port=4545'\r\n      - '--http.api=engine,web3,eth,net,personal,miner,txpool,debug,admin'\r\n      - '--ws'\r\n      - '--ws.addr=0.0.0.0'\r\n      - '--ws.port=4546'\r\n      - '--ws.origins=*'\r\n      - '--ws.api=engine,web3,eth,net,personal,miner,txpool,debug,admin'\r\n      - '--authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0'\r\n      - '--authrpc.port=8551'\r\n      - '--authrpc.vhosts=*'\r\n      - '--authrpc.jwtsecret=/jwt/jwt.hex'\r\n      - '--http.vhosts=*'\r\n      - '--http.corsdomain=*'\r\n      - '--metrics'\r\n      - '--metrics.addr=0.0.0.0'\r\n      - '--metrics.port=6040'\r\n      - '--pprof'\r\n      - '--pprof.addr=0.0.0.0'\r\n      - '--pprof.port=6041'\r\n    volumes:\r\n      - /md0/geth-fast/data:/data\r\n      - /md0/geth-fast/jwt:/jwt\r\n    restart: unless-stopped\r\n    network_mode: host\r\n\r\n  prysm:\r\n    image: prysmaticlabs/prysm-beacon-chain:v3.2.0\r\n    container_name: eth-prysm\r\n    command:\r\n      - '--mainnet'\r\n      - '--datadir=/data'\r\n      - '--http-web3provider=http://127.0.0.1:4545'\r\n      - '--rpc-host=0.0.0.0'\r\n      - '--rpc-port=9547'\r\n      - '--monitoring-host=0.0.0.0'\r\n      - '--execution-endpoint=http://127.0.0.1:8551'\r\n      - '--jwt-secret=/jwt/jwt.hex'\r\n      - '--accept-terms-of-use'\r\n      - '--grpc-gateway-host=0.0.0.0'\r\n      - '--grpc-gateway-corsdomain=*'\r\n      - '--checkpoint-sync-url=https://beaconstate.info/'\r\n      - '--genesis-beacon-api-url=https://beaconstate.info/'\r\n    volumes:\r\n      - /md0/geth-fast/prysm:/data\r\n      - /md0/geth-fast/jwt:/jwt\r\n    network_mode: host\r\n    restart: unless-stopped\r\n```\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis caused my node using 100% CPU in the pebble compacting(see the profile file for more detail)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"528\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3627395/219393112-f7212d5a-5b6e-44fc-a2ac-e01706afc789.png\">\r\n\r\n[pprof.geth.samples.cpu.003.pb.gz](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/files/10756962/pprof.geth.samples.cpu.003.pb.gz)\r\n\r\nSeems we are using all the CPU for compaction here https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/13d7de77f40b2c2bdcece96a06f6b7f89c0026cf/ethdb/pebble/pebble.go#L167\r\n\r\n\r\nYes, I can set `--cpu=2` to limit the CPU quota in docker container, but it can't take an effort on pebble's side, so IMHO\r\n\r\n1. use https://github.com/uber-go/automaxprocs to set the correct CPU quota?\r\n2. set with command line argument?\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n\r\nWhen submitting logs: please submit them as text and not screenshots.\r\n",
